# dh-golang + golang-go intentionally NOT listed here.  Why:
# dh-golang auto-registers a configure hook that stages source
# under obj-<triplet>/src/<importpath>/ and sets GOPATH= to the
# obj-... root — regardless of `--with=golang` / `--buildsystem=
# golang` on the dh line.  The configure-staging then drops
# //go:embed sibling files (schema.sql, oses.yaml, runbooks/,
# builtin/*.skill.yaml) and switches go into GOPATH mode, which
# can't resolve our module-mode imports ("cannot find package
# .../internal/cli in any of /work/obj-.../src/...").  Our
# `override_dh_auto_build: $(MAKE) build` already drives Go via
# the project Makefile (CGO_ENABLED=0, -trimpath, the works);
# we don't need dh-golang at all, and removing it from
# Build-Depends keeps it from auto-attaching.  golang-go also
# removed: the deb-builder image installs Go 1.26 manually from
# go.dev/dl/ (Debian 12 ships 1.21 max) and apt's golang-go
# would shadow that on PATH.  See run_pkg_build_testing.sh
# already passing `-d` to dpkg-buildpackage to skip
# Build-Depends checking — same rationale.
