Package: pg-hardstorage
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 pg-hardstorage-common (= ${source:Version}),
 adduser
Recommends:
 postgresql-client (>= 13)
Suggests:
 pg-hardstorage-server,
 systemd
Description: PostgreSQL backup, done right -- agent and CLI
 pg_hardstorage performs incremental, content-addressed backups of
 PostgreSQL clusters with WAL archiving and point-in-time recovery.
 It is a single static Go binary that doubles as a long-running
 host agent and as an interactive CLI.
 .
 This package ships the pg_hardstorage binary, shell completions,
 manpages, and a systemd unit suitable for single- or multi-tenant
 hosts.

Package: pg-hardstorage-common
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends}
Description: PostgreSQL backup, done right -- shared data
 Architecture-independent assets shared by every pg-hardstorage
 binary package: runbooks, OpenAPI documents, and the v1 JSON
 schema files that govern manifests and audit records.
 .
 Install pg-hardstorage to get the agent and CLI.

Package: pg-hardstorage-server
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 pg-hardstorage (= ${binary:Version})
Description: PostgreSQL backup, done right -- control-plane server
 Stub package for the v0.5 control-plane server. Installing this
 package today is a no-op other than registering the dependency on
 pg-hardstorage; the server binary lands with v0.5 and unlocks the
 multi-host orchestration API plus the centralised retention engine.

Package: pg-hardstorage-compat-pgbackrest
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 pg-hardstorage (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: pgbackrest
Description: pg_hardstorage drop-in shim for pgBackRest
 Drop-in replacement binary that mimics the pgBackRest CLI surface
 (8 verbs: stanza-create, backup, restore, archive-push, archive-get,
 info, check, verify) so existing cron jobs, archive_command lines,
 and monitoring scripts keep working but produce native pg_hardstorage
 backups.
 .
 Installs the pg-hardstorage-pgbackrest binary at /usr/bin and offers
 a Conflicts with the upstream pgbackrest package so the operator
 picks one or the other. Symlink /usr/local/bin/pgbackrest to this
 binary for true PATH-level drop-in.
 .
 See /usr/share/doc/pg-hardstorage-compat-pgbackrest/migration.md
 for the cutover playbook.

Package: pg-hardstorage-compat-barman
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 pg-hardstorage (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: barman, barman-cli
Description: pg_hardstorage drop-in shim for Barman
 Drop-in replacement binaries that mimic the Barman CLI surface
 (7 verbs: backup, recover, list-backup, show-backup, check, delete,
 plus a separate barman-wal-archive binary for archive_command use).
 .
 Installs pg-hardstorage-barman and pg-hardstorage-barman-wal-archive
 at /usr/bin and offers a Conflicts with the upstream barman + barman-cli
 packages so the operator picks one or the other. Symlink
 /usr/local/bin/{barman,barman-wal-archive} to these binaries for true
 PATH-level drop-in.
 .
 See /usr/share/doc/pg-hardstorage-compat-barman/migration.md
 for the cutover playbook.

Package: pg-hardstorage-compat-walg
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 pg-hardstorage (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: wal-g
Description: pg_hardstorage drop-in shim for WAL-G
 Drop-in replacement binary that mimics the WAL-G CLI surface
 (5 verbs: backup-push, backup-fetch, backup-list, wal-push,
 wal-fetch) so existing cron jobs, archive_command lines, and
 monitoring scripts keep working but produce native pg_hardstorage
 backups.
 .
 Configuration follows WAL-G's env-var convention (WALG_S3_PREFIX,
 PGHOST, ...).  Installs pg-hardstorage-walg at /usr/bin and offers
 a Conflicts with the upstream wal-g package so the operator picks
 one or the other.  Symlink /usr/local/bin/wal-g to this binary for
 true PATH-level drop-in.
 .
 See /usr/share/doc/pg-hardstorage-compat-walg/migration.md
 for the cutover playbook.
